{
  "uuid": "e42308cbe87adcc52c32d04ead99e8ee",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "R&D Assistant Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><em><strong>To assist in all aspects of dyeing and finishing crocodile leather, from developing and testing new recipes to troubleshooting production issues, with the goal of achieving a high-quality end product that meets industry standards.</strong></em></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>This involves working with various processes, techniques, and materials, as well as participating in daily production and development activities.</strong></em></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Assist in dyeing and finishing methods, including fatliquoring, re-tanning, dyeing and chrome- and metal-free processes and techniques; and finishing techniques; treating crocodile leather from different species.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Assist in ensuring a high-quality end-product from Crust to Finish, according to the highest industry standards and specific properties.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Assist to develop, improve and test new recipes.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Assist to develop new articles.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Assist to monitor production batches for recipe and process fine tuning.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Troubleshoot production issues, propose and implement action plan.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Plan and monitor development activities for both production orders and R&amp;D projects.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Analyse data and create reports pertaining R&amp;D projects and production topics.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Use the R&amp;D tracker to constantly update, track and archive recipes and samples.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Involved in daily production and development operations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>JOB REQUIREMENTS</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>At least 5 years of experience in Tannery</p>\n<p>Good communication skills, in both verbal and writing</p>\n<p>Technical experience is essential</p>\n<p>Knowledge of hazardous substances is essential</p>\n<p>Good knowledge of Microsoft Office</p>\n<p>Good color sense</p>\n<p>Creative</p>\n<p>Able to perform in a high pressure environment with the ability to achieve objectives with tight deadlines</p>",
